# Route Handler Rules

Route handlers must stay thin.

Allowed in routes:

- request parsing
- schema validation
- calling services
- returning responses

Not allowed:

- lifecycle logic
- permission decisions
- complex branching
- database mutations for domain logic

Bad:

PATCH /documents/:id
sets publishedAt directly

Good:

POST /documents/:id/publish
-> documentService.publishDocument()